SARIMA Model Dataset Description – Critical Load Forecasting (2023)

File: RnD_CriticalLoadHistory_2023.xlsx
Format: Excel file (.xlsx)
Time Resolution: Every 15 minutes
Total Duration: January 1, 2023 to December 31, 2023
Total Records: 35,040 rows (365 days × 96 intervals/day)

Columns:
1. Timestamp
   - Format: MM/DD/YY HH:MM
   - Example: 1/1/23 0:00, 1/1/23 0:15, ...
   - Marks the beginning of each 15-minute interval

2. Very Critical Loads
   - Unit: kilowatt-hours (kWh)
   - Description: High-priority systems (e.g., core infrastructure, safety-critical)

3. Medium Critical Loads
   - Unit: kilowatt-hours (kWh)
   - Description: Systems with medium operational priority

4. Low Critical Loads
   - Unit: kilowatt-hours (kWh)
   - Description: Lower-priority or auxiliary loads (e.g., lighting, environment)

Notes:
- The second row in the Excel file contains unit labels ("kWh") and must be skipped (`skiprows=1`).
- All numeric values use a comma (",") as the decimal separator and must be converted to dot (".") before processing.
- Each load category is treated as a separate univariate time series.
- The file is used by both SARIMA and LSTM forecasting models.

Sample (first 8 rows):

| Timestamp     | Very Critical | Medium Critical | Low Critical |
|---------------|----------------|------------------|----------------|
| 1/1/23 0:00    | 0,15           | 0,06             | 0,08           |
| 1/1/23 0:15    | 0,16           | 0,07             | 0,08           |
| 1/1/23 0:30    | 0,15           | 0,09             | 0,08           |
| 1/1/23 0:45    | 0,16           | 0,08             | 0,07           |
| 1/1/23 1:00    | 0,16           | 0,07             | 0,07           |
| 1/1/23 1:15    | 0,16           | 0,07             | 0,08           |
| 1/1/23 1:30    | 0,14           | 0,06             | 0,07           |
| 1/1/23 1:45    | 0,16           | 0,09             | 0,08           |

